&quot;Never underestimate the power of human stupidity.&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ikagawa>Ikagawa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#660000>(10/29/02 8:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2148.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.insightbb.com/~claybats/images/avatars/mt_11.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cheapest way to raise nano skills?</span><hr size=1> Also, remember to cast Int Boost on yourself beforehand. That will kick up your nano skills a few pts. <p>Bellerephon<br>
