<br>
I'm presuming that you are either Opifex or Solitus, which means that your Int cost is 2.0, so you are looking at somewhere around 16,000 IP to go from ~186 to ~226.  So in the short run (next level), it will almost certainly be cheaper to simply raise the two nano skills by +8.<br>
<br>
In the LONG run, however, if you want to keep your nano skills at their best (and you DO), it is ALWAYS more cost effective to keep your Int maxed, since every 5 pts of Int raises <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>every</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> nano skill by +1.  You also get some trickle down to things like Comp Lit, Treatment, First Aid, etc.  In fact, if you had been keeping your Int maxed instead of only raising PsyMod, TS, and SI (and BM) individually, it's possible that you could probably have started using Vulnerability Seeker a level or two ago. But now you know. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- iccusion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=publius@thepunchingbag74708>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kung Fu MASTAH</span><br>  Posts: 654<br> <font color=#660000>(10/30/02 6:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2148.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cheapest way to raise nano skills?</span><hr size=1> I am of the opinion that every toon, of every race, of every class, should always max Intelligence, every time they level.<br>
